  <description><![CDATA[<p><span>Voted as one of Tripadvisor's Traveller's Choice Top 25 hotels in <a data-udi="umb://document/52fab17731fa49639f8a0841e064a064" href="/{localLink:umb://document/52fab17731fa49639f8a0841e064a064}" title="Switzerland">Switzerland</a> and o</span><span>ne</span> of <a data-udi="umb://document/7e163ac5c9114f0dae9f3f8d222fa730" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7e163ac5c9114f0dae9f3f8d222fa730}" title="Wengen">Wengen’s</a> leading hotels, the Beausite Park Hotel and Spa offers high standards of both service and cuisine, has a refined atmosphere and receives consistently good feedback from guests.</p>
<h2>Family friendly </h2>
<p>The Beausite is a family friendly property and offers a range of services that you and your family can make the most of during your stay. Families can make the most of the swimming pool, or take some time to unwind in the playroom. There is a children's menu available as well, just ask the restaurant staff on your arrival.  For families with younger children, baby phones are available, so you can head down for a later dinner if you wish. </p>
<h2>Restaurant and bar </h2>
<p>Whilst you are away you can enjoy meals made with fresh and regional ingredients, sourced from local suppliers. A regional buffet breakfast can be enjoyed in the restaurant with fresh pastries and breads, local Alpine cheeses and meats and live cooking for egg dishes. Dinner includes a four course Beausite menu with high quality ingredients. The hotel caters well for dietary requirements upon request, so everyone can enjoy their meals on holiday.  The Rondo Bar is a great spot to catch up with friends and family, whether its with <span>an apertif before dinner or a nightcap after a relaxing day in Wengen.</span></p>
<h2>Spa and wellness facilities </h2>
<p>Treat yourself to some down time and make the most of the hotels spa and wellness facilities. With access to a swimming pool, whirlpool, jacuzzi, sauna, steam bath and fitness room gym, you really are spoilt for choice when it comes to unwinding after an active day. For an extra treat, massages and facials are available to bookable through the reception. </p>
<h3>Why is this an Inghams' Choice property?</h3>
<p><strong>Great facilities for children</strong> - With access to a children's play room and an indoor swimming pool, there are plenty of ways to keep the children entertained at Hotel Beausite when you're not on the mountains. </p>
<p><strong>Relaxation facilities for adults</strong> - Treat yourself to some 'you' time and book a massage of facial. Or simply sit back and unwind in the jacuzzi or steam room. </p>
<p><strong>Gastronomy</strong> - Enjoy a dinner date with the mountains. Try a range of carefully made regional Swiss dishes at the hotels restaurant with some fantastic views of the Jungfrau peaks.</p>]]></description>
